[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Russia beat France 45-41 to win the men's Olympic foil team gold medal on Friday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The trio of Timur Safin, Alexey Cheremisinov and Artur Akhmatkhuzin trailed for long spells but fought back to secure Russia's third gold of the fencing events - and sixth in total.
The United States took the bronze medal with a 45-31 victory over defending champions Italy.
The US now have three fencing medals at these Games, level with Hungary.
